swMibModule.name: swMibModule

revisions.description: The initial version of this module.
Added swIDIDMode to the swFabric group.

Added object for Trap Severity Level, swFwLastSeverityLevel. Added the enumeration swFwResourceFlash for SwFwClassesAreas. Deprecated the mib object swEventTrapLevel. Updated the description of swGroupId and corrected the spell mistakes. Obsoleted the swFault Trap. Added enumerations four-GB for swFCPortSpeed and unknown, other for swFCPortType.
Added swFCPortSpecifier object to swFCPortTable.
Modified the #SUMMARY and #ARGUMENTS for swFabricWatchTrap
1. Modified the description for swPortTrunked 2. Updated the SW Traps summary and description to remove the obsolete varbindings
Added swFCPortFlag object to swFCPortTable
Added enumerations eight-GB and ten-GB for swFCPortSpeed
Included swFCPortFlag as an additiional variable binding for trap SWFCPortScn
Added enumerations octuple and decuple for swNbBaudRate
Added the enumerations swFwEPortUtil and swFwEPortPktl for swFwClassAreaIndex
Added swFCPortBrcdType object to swFCPortTable
Added Toptalker support and swVfId to the swFabric group.
Added swIPv6ChangeTrap, swIPv6Address and swIPv6Status .
Added swModel to distiguish between 7500 and 7500E switch .
Added the enumerations swFwPortLr, swFwEPortLr, swFwEPortUtil, swFwEPortPktl, swFwFCUPortLr, swFwFOPPortLr for swFwClassAreaIndex.
Added swPmgrEventTrap information.
Added additional fabric watch threshold in SwFwActs.
Added port phy states.
Added swEventVfId in swEventTable.
Removed the version information from Brocade's proprietary MIB file name.
Modified swVfid position at the last of swFabric table
Added swFwCPUMemUsage enumeration under swFwClassAreaIndex.

Updated the description of swCpuAction/swMemAction and access of swcpuormemoryusage objects and changed the type of swEndDeviceInvalidWord, swEndDeviceLinkFailure,swEndDeviceSyncLoss, swEndDeviceSigLoss, swEndDeviceProtoErr,swEndDeviceInvalidCRC from integer32 to counter32.
Added swFabricReconfigTrap and swFabricSegmentTrap.
Removed enum switchReboot from swAdmStatus.
Changed swFwCustUnit access to read-only
Added enums swFwEPortTrunkUtil,swFwFCUPortTrunkUtil and swFwFOPPortTrunkUtil in SwFwClassesAreas
Added swConnUnitExtensionTable and entries for 64 bit portstats.
Added swMemUsageLimit1 and swMemUsageLimit3 under swCpuOrMemoryUsage
Added swExttrap as internal trap.
Changed the descriptions for swConnUnitExtensionTable.
Obsoleted swGroupTable, swGroupMemTable from swGroup.
Added swFCPortWwn, swFCPortBrcdType in swFcPortScn and added swStateChangeTrap
Added trap swPortMoveTrap
Added trap portStats objects under SwConnUnitPortStatEntry
Added trap swBrcdGenericTrap
Added swVfName
Added swPortConfigTable
Added swFCPortPrevType in swFCPortScn
Added fifty filter classes under swFwClassAreaIndex
Updated the description of swBrcdTrapBitMask and swBrcdGenericTrap for Fapwwn Trap
Deprecated swAgtCmtyTable and provided support of standard mibs SnmpCommunityTable and snmpTargetParamsTable and snmpTargetAddrTable
Updated the datatype for swPortEncrypt and swPortCompression
Added enumeration sexdecuple for swNbBaudRate
Added a new value lowBufferCrsd(7) for swFwLastEvent
Changed the area name filter-fmcfg to filterFmCfg in SwFwClassesAreas
Included FDMI event case in swBrcdTrapBitMask
Added class3 discards error in SwConnUnitPortStatEntry
Moved swPortConfigTable, CiperMode and Encrypt/CompressStatus to faext.mib
Changed fportmode(2) to portmode(2) for object swTopTalkerMntMode.
Added swauthProtocolPassword and swauthProtocolPassword for IBM DirectorServer applications
Added new enum noSigDet(14) for object swFCPortPhyState
Changed the syntax of swCpuAction and swMemAction objects.
Added PCS block errors in swConnUnitPortStatEntry
Added swDeviceStatus and swDeviceStatusTrap
Added sixteenGB support to swFCPortSpeed and also deprecated teh same
Added an area filterFmCfg51 in the class SwFwClassesAreas
Removed the tab space and added the space key for swFCPortEntry 38 as this caused a crash in MIB browser
Added swFCPortDisableReason in SwFCPortEntry and swFCPortScn trap.
Added unroutable frame counter in swConnUnitPortStatEntry
Made the swFCPortSpeed obsolete
Changed the description for swVFName and swConnUnitPCSErrorCounter
Updated swFCPortCapacity description
Added swFwPowerOnHours in SwFwClassesAreas
Updated the description for swCpuUsageLimit, swCpuAction, swMemAction, swMemUsageLimit1 and swMemUsageLimit3.
Added FEC Counters swConnUnitFECCorrectedCounter, swConnUnitFECUnCorrectedCounter
Added swZoneConfigChangeTrap

swOperStatus.name: swOperStatus
swOperStatus.description: The current operational status of the switch. The states are as follow: o online(1) means the switch is accessible by an external Fibre Channel port; o offline(2) means the switch is not accessible; o testing(3) means the switch is in a built-in test mode and is not accessible by an external Fibre Channel port; o faulty(4) means the switch is not operational.

swAdmStatus.name: swAdmStatus
swAdmStatus.description: The desired administrative status of the switch. A management station may place the switch in a desired state by setting this object accordingly. The states are as follow: o online(1) means set the switch to be accessible by an external Fibre Channel port; o offline(2) means set the switch to be inaccessible; o testing(3) means set the switch to run the built-in test; o faulty(4) means set the switch to a 'soft' faulty condition; o reboot(5) means set the switch to reboot in 1 second. o fastboot(6) means set the switch to fastboot in 1 second. Fastboot would cause the switch to boot but skip over the POST. When the switch is in faulty state, only two states can be set: faulty and reboot/fastboot.

swTelnetShellAdmStatus.name: swTelnetShellAdmStatus
swTelnetShellAdmStatus.description: The desired administrative status of the Telnet shell. By setting it to terminated(1), the current Telnet shell task is deleted. When this variable instance is read, it reports the value last set through SNMP.

swSsn.name: swSsn
swSsn.description: The soft serial number of the switch.

swFlashDLOperStatus.name: swFlashDLOperStatus
swFlashDLOperStatus.description: The operational status of the FLASH. The operational states are as follow: o swCurrent(1) indicates that the FLASH contains the current firmware image or config file; o swFwUpgraded(2) state indicates that it contains the image upgraded from the swFlashDLHost.0.; o swCfUploaded(3) state indicates that the switch configuration file has been uploaded to the host; and o swCfDownloaded(4) state indicates that the switch configuration file has been downloaded from the host. o swFwCorrupted (5) state indicates that the firmware in the FLASH of the switch is corrupted.

swFlashDLAdmStatus.name: swFlashDLAdmStatus
swFlashDLAdmStatus.description: The desired state of the FLASH. A management station may place the FLASH in a desired state by setting this object accordingly: o swCurrent(1) indicates that the FLASH contains the current firmware image or config file; o swFwUpgrade(2) means that the firmware in the FLASH is to be upgraded from the host specified; o swCfUpload(3) means that the switch config file is to be uploaded to the host specified; or o swCfDownload(4) means that the switch config file is to be downloaded from the host specified. o swFwCorrupted(5) state indicates that the firmware in the FLASH is corrupted. This value is for informational purpose only. However, set of swFlashDLAdmStatus to this value is not allowed. The host is specified in swFlashDLHost.0. In addition, user name is specified in swFlashDLUser.0, and the file name specified in swFlashDLFile.0. Reference the user manual on the following commands, o firmwareDownload, o configUpload, and o configDownload.

swFlashDLHost.name: swFlashDLHost
swFlashDLHost.description: The name or IP address (in dot notation) of the host to download or upload a relevant file to the FLASH.

swFlashDLUser.name: swFlashDLUser
swFlashDLUser.description: The user name on the host to download or upload a relevant file to or from the FLASH.

swFlashDLFile.name: swFlashDLFile
swFlashDLFile.description: The name of the file to be downloaded or uploaded.

swFlashDLPassword.name: swFlashDLPassword
swFlashDLPassword.description: The password to be used in for FTP transfer of files in the download or upload operation.

swBeaconOperStatus.name: swBeaconOperStatus
swBeaconOperStatus.description: The current operational status of the switch beacon. When the beacon is on, the LEDs on the front panel of the switch run alternately from left to right and right to left. The color is yellow. When the beacon is off, each LED will be in their its regular status indicating color and state.

swBeaconAdmStatus.name: swBeaconAdmStatus
swBeaconAdmStatus.description: The desired status of the switch beacon. When the beacon is set to on, the LEDs on the front panel of the switch run alternately from left to right and right to left. The color is yellow. When the beacon is set to off, each LED will be in its regular status indicating color and state.

swDiagResult.name: swDiagResult
swDiagResult.description: The result of the power-on startup (POST) diagnostics.

swNumSensors.name: swNumSensors
swNumSensors.description: The number of sensors inside the switch.

swSensorEntry.name: swSensorEntry
swSensorEntry.description: An entry of the sensor information.

swSensorType.name: swSensorType
swSensorType.description: This object identifies the sensor type.

swSensorStatus.name: swSensorStatus
swSensorStatus.description: The current status of the sensor.

swSensorValue.name: swSensorValue
swSensorValue.description: The current value (reading) of the sensor. The value, -2147483648, represents an unknown quantity. It also means that the sensor does not have the capability to measure the actual value. In V2.0, the temperature sensor value will be in Celsius; the fan value will be in RPM (revolution per minute); and the power supply sensor reading will be unknown.

swSensorInfo.name: swSensorInfo
swSensorInfo.description: Additional displayable information on the sensor. In V2.x, it contains the sensor type and number in textual format. For example, 'Temp 3', 'Fan 6'.

swTrackChangesInfo.name: swTrackChangesInfo
swTrackChangesInfo.description: Track changes string. For trap only

swID.name: swID
swID.description: The number of the logical switch (0/1)

swEtherIPAddress.name: swEtherIPAddress
swEtherIPAddress.description: The IP Address of the Ethernet interface of this logical switch.

swEtherIPMask.name: swEtherIPMask
swEtherIPMask.description: The IP Mask of the Ethernet interface of this logical switch.

swFCIPAddress.name: swFCIPAddress
swFCIPAddress.description: The IP Address of the FC interface of this logical switch.

swFCIPMask.name: swFCIPMask
swFCIPMask.description: The IP Mask of the FC interface of this logical switch.

swIPv6Status.name: swIPv6Status
swIPv6Status.description: The current status of ipv6 address.

swModel.name: swModel
swModel.description: Indicates whether the switch is 7500 or 7500E .

swTestString.name: swTestString
swTestString.description: presence of this string represents test trap.

swPortList.name: swPortList
swPortList.description: This string represents the list of ports and its WWN when ports moved from one switch to another.

swBrcdTrapBitMask.name: swBrcdTrapBitMask
swBrcdTrapBitMask.description: Type of notification will be represented by a single bit in this variable. 0x01 - Fabric change event 0x02 - Device change event 0x04 - Fapwwn change event 0x08 - FDMI events.

swFCPortPrevType.name: swFCPortPrevType
swFCPortPrevType.description: This represents port type of a port before it goes online/offline and it is valid only in swFcPortSCN trap

swDeviceStatus.name: swDeviceStatus
swDeviceStatus.description: This represents the attached device status. The status will change whenever port/node goes to online/offline

swDomainID.name: swDomainID
swDomainID.description: The current Fibre Channel domain ID of the switch. To set a new value, the switch (swAdmStatus) must be in offline or testing state.

swPrincipalSwitch.name: swPrincipalSwitch
swPrincipalSwitch.description: This object indicates whether the switch is the Principal switch as per FC-SW.

swNumNbs.name: swNumNbs
swNumNbs.description: The number of Inter-Switch Links in the (immediate) neighborhood.

swNbTable.name: swNbTable
swNbTable.description: This table contains the ISLs in the immediate neighborhood of the switch.

swNbEntry.name: swNbEntry
swNbEntry.description: An entry containing each neighbor ISL parameters.

swNbIndex.name: swNbIndex
swNbIndex.description: This object identifies the neighbor ISL entry.

swNbMyPort.name: swNbMyPort
swNbMyPort.description: This is the port that has an ISL to another switch.

swNbRemDomain.name: swNbRemDomain
swNbRemDomain.description: This is the Fibre Channel domain on the other end of the ISL.

swNbRemPort.name: swNbRemPort
swNbRemPort.description: This is the port index on the other end of the ISL.

swNbBaudRate.name: swNbBaudRate
swNbBaudRate.description: The baud rate of the ISL.

swNbIslState.name: swNbIslState
swNbIslState.description: The current state of the ISL. The swNbIslState will be 0 when ISL is in incompatible state or port is a slave port.

swNbIslCost.name: swNbIslCost
swNbIslCost.description: The current link cost of the ISL.

swNbRemPortName.name: swNbRemPortName
swNbRemPortName.description: The World_wide_Name of the remote port.

swFabricMemTable.name: swFabricMemTable
swFabricMemTable.description: This table contains information on the member switches of a fabric. This may not be available on all versions of Fabric OS.

swFabricMemEntry.name: swFabricMemEntry
swFabricMemEntry.description: An entry containing each switch in the fabric.

swFabricMemWwn.name: swFabricMemWwn
swFabricMemWwn.description: This object identifies the World wide name of the member switch.

swFabricMemDid.name: swFabricMemDid
swFabricMemDid.description: This object identifies the domain id of the member switch.

swFabricMemName.name: swFabricMemName
swFabricMemName.description: This object identifies the name of the member switch.

swFabricMemEIP.name: swFabricMemEIP
swFabricMemEIP.description: This object identifies the ethernet IP address of the member switch.

swFabricMemFCIP.name: swFabricMemFCIP
swFabricMemFCIP.description: This object identifies the Fibre Channel IP address of the member switch.

swFabricMemGWIP.name: swFabricMemGWIP
swFabricMemGWIP.description: This object identifies the Gateway IP address of the member switch.

swFabricMemType.name: swFabricMemType
swFabricMemType.description: This object identifies the member switch type.

swFabricMemShortVersion.name: swFabricMemShortVersion
swFabricMemShortVersion.description: This object identifies Fabric OS version of the member switch.

swIDIDMode.name: swIDIDMode
swIDIDMode.description: Status of Insistent Domain ID (IDID) mode. Status indicating IDID mode is enabled or not.

swPmgrEventTime.name: swPmgrEventTime
swPmgrEventTime.description: This object identifies the date and time when this pmgr event occurred, in textual format.

swPmgrEventDescr.name: swPmgrEventDescr
swPmgrEventDescr.description: This object identifies the textual description of the pmgr event.

swVfName.name: swVfName
swVfName.description: This represents the virtual fabric name configured in the switch

swAgtCmtyTable.name: swAgtCmtyTable
swAgtCmtyTable.description: A table that contains, one entry for each Community, the access control and parameters of the Community.

swauthProtocolPassword.name: swauthProtocolPassword
swauthProtocolPassword.description: This entry is created specific to the Pharos switch to change the password for the auth protocol to reserved user DirectorServerSNMPv3User

swprivProtocolPassword.name: swprivProtocolPassword
swprivProtocolPassword.description: This entry is created specific to the Pharos switch to change the password for the priv protocol to reserved user DirectorServerSNMPv3User

swAgtCmtyEntry.name: swAgtCmtyEntry
swAgtCmtyEntry.description: An entry containing the Community parameters.

swAgtCmtyIdx.name: swAgtCmtyIdx
swAgtCmtyIdx.description: This object identifies the SNMPv1 Community entry.

swAgtCmtyStr.name: swAgtCmtyStr
swAgtCmtyStr.description: This is a Community string supported by the agent. If a new value is set successfully, it takes effect immediately.

swAgtTrapRcp.name: swAgtTrapRcp
swAgtTrapRcp.description: This is the trap recipient associated with the Community. If a new value is set successfully, it takes effect immediately.

swAgtTrapSeverityLevel.name: swAgtTrapSeverityLevel
swAgtTrapSeverityLevel.description: This is the trap severity level associated with the swAgtTrapRcp. The trap severity level in conjunction with the an event's severity level. When an event occurs and if its severity level is at or below the set value, the SNMP trap is sent to configured trap recipients. The severity level is limited to particular events. If a new value is set successfully, it takes effect immediately.

swFCPortCapacity.name: swFCPortCapacity
swFCPortCapacity.description: The maximum number of of physical ports on the switch. This will include ports of the protocol: FC, FCIP(GE ports), VE(FCIP)...

swFCPortTable.name: swFCPortTable
swFCPortTable.description: A table that contains, one entry for each switch port, configuration and service parameters of the port.

swFCPortEntry.name: swFCPortEntry
swFCPortEntry.description: An entry containing the configuration and service parameters of the switch port.

swFCPortIndex.name: swFCPortIndex
swFCPortIndex.description: This object identifies the switch port index. Note that the value of a port index is 1 higher than the port number labeled on the front panel. E.g. port index 1 correspond to port number 0.

swFCPortType.name: swFCPortType
swFCPortType.description: This object identifies the type of switch port. It may be of type stitch(1), flannel(2), loom(3) , bloom(4),rdbloom(5) or wormhole(6).

swFCPortPhyState.name: swFCPortPhyState
swFCPortPhyState.description: This object identifies the physical state of the port: noCard(1) no card present in this switch slot; noTransceiver(2) no Transceiver module in this port. noGbic(2) was used previously. Transceiver is the generic name for GBIC, SFP etc.; laserFault(3) the module is signaling a laser fault (defective Transceiver); noLight(4) the module is not receiving light; noSync(5) the module is receiving light but is out of sync; inSync(6) the module is receiving light and is in sync; portFault(7) the port is marked faulty (defective Transceiver, cable or device); diagFault(8) the port failed diagnostics (defective G_Port or FL_Port card or motherboard); lockRef(9) the port is locking to the reference signal. validating(10) Validation is in progress invalidModule(11) Invalid SFP unknown(255) unknown.

swFCPortOpStatus.name: swFCPortOpStatus
swFCPortOpStatus.description: This object identifies the operational status of the port. The online(1) state indicates that user frames can be passed. The unknown(0) state indicates that likely the port module is physically absent (see swFCPortPhyState).

swFCPortAdmStatus.name: swFCPortAdmStatus
swFCPortAdmStatus.description: The desired state of the port. A management station may place the port in a desired state by setting this object accordingly. The testing(3) state indicates that no user frames can be passed. As the result of either explicit management action or per configuration information accessible by the switch, swFCPortAdmStatus is then changed to either the online(1) or testing(3) states, or remains in the offline(2) state.

swFCPortLinkState.name: swFCPortLinkState
swFCPortLinkState.description: This object indicates the link state of the port. The value may be: enabled(1) - port is allowed to participate in the FC-PH protocol with its attached port (or ports if it is in a FC-AL loop); disabled(2) - the port is not allowed to participate in the FC-PH protocol with its attached port(s); loopback(3) - the port may transmit frames through an internal path to verify the health of the transmitter and receiver path. Note that when the port's link state changes, its operational status (swFCPortOpStatus) will be affected.

swFCPortTxType.name: swFCPortTxType
swFCPortTxType.description: This object indicates the media transmitter type of the port. The value may be: unknown(1) cannot determined to the port driver lw(2) long wave laser sw(3) short wave laser ld(4) long wave LED cu(5) copper (electrical).

swFCPortTxWords.name: swFCPortTxWords
swFCPortTxWords.description: This object counts the number of Fibre Channel words that the port has transmitted.

swFCPortRxWords.name: swFCPortRxWords
swFCPortRxWords.description: This object counts the number of Fibre Channel words that the port has received.

swFCPortTxFrames.name: swFCPortTxFrames
swFCPortTxFrames.description: This object counts the number of (Fibre Channel) frames that the port has transmitted.

swFCPortRxFrames.name: swFCPortRxFrames
swFCPortRxFrames.description: This object counts the number of (Fibre Channel) frames that the port has received.

swFCPortRxC2Frames.name: swFCPortRxC2Frames
swFCPortRxC2Frames.description: This object counts the number of Class 2 frames that the port has received.

swFCPortRxC3Frames.name: swFCPortRxC3Frames
swFCPortRxC3Frames.description: This object counts the number of Class 3 frames that the port has received.

swFCPortRxLCs.name: swFCPortRxLCs
swFCPortRxLCs.description: This object counts the number of Link Control frames that the port has received.

swFCPortRxMcasts.name: swFCPortRxMcasts
swFCPortRxMcasts.description: This object counts the number of Multicast frames that the port has received.

swFCPortTooManyRdys.name: swFCPortTooManyRdys
swFCPortTooManyRdys.description: This object counts the number of times when RDYs exceeds the frames received.

swFCPortNoTxCredits.name: swFCPortNoTxCredits
swFCPortNoTxCredits.description: This object counts the number of times when the transmit credit has reached zero.

swFCPortRxEncInFrs.name: swFCPortRxEncInFrs
swFCPortRxEncInFrs.description: This object counts the number of encoding error or disparity error inside frames received.

swFCPortRxCrcs.name: swFCPortRxCrcs
swFCPortRxCrcs.description: This object counts the number of CRC errors detected for frames received.

swFCPortRxTruncs.name: swFCPortRxTruncs
swFCPortRxTruncs.description: This object counts the number of truncated frames that the port has received.

swFCPortRxTooLongs.name: swFCPortRxTooLongs
swFCPortRxTooLongs.description: This object counts the number of received frames that are too long.

swFCPortRxBadEofs.name: swFCPortRxBadEofs
swFCPortRxBadEofs.description: This object counts the number of received frames that have bad EOF delimiter.

swFCPortRxEncOutFrs.name: swFCPortRxEncOutFrs
swFCPortRxEncOutFrs.description: This object counts the number of encoding error or disparity error outside frames received.

swFCPortRxBadOs.name: swFCPortRxBadOs
swFCPortRxBadOs.description: This object counts the number of invalid Ordered Sets received.

swFCPortC3Discards.name: swFCPortC3Discards
swFCPortC3Discards.description: This object counts the number of Class 3 frames that the port has discarded.

swFCPortMcastTimedOuts.name: swFCPortMcastTimedOuts
swFCPortMcastTimedOuts.description: This object counts the number of Multicast frames that has been timed out.

swFCPortTxMcasts.name: swFCPortTxMcasts
swFCPortTxMcasts.description: This object counts the number of Multicast frames that has been transmitted.

swFCPortLipIns.name: swFCPortLipIns
swFCPortLipIns.description: This object counts the number of Loop Initializations that has been initiated by loop devices attached.

swFCPortLipOuts.name: swFCPortLipOuts
swFCPortLipOuts.description: This object counts the number of Loop Initializations that has been initiated by the port.

swFCPortLipLastAlpa.name: swFCPortLipLastAlpa
swFCPortLipLastAlpa.description: This object indicates the Physical Address (AL_PA) of the loop device that initiated the last Loop Initialization.

swFCPortWwn.name: swFCPortWwn
swFCPortWwn.description: The World_wide_Name of the Fibre Channel port. The contents of an instance are in the IEEE extended format as specified in FC-PH; the 12-bit port identifier represents the port number within the switch.

swFCPortSpeed.name: swFCPortSpeed
swFCPortSpeed.description: The desired baud rate for the port. It can have the values of 1GB (1), 2GB (2), Auto-Negotiate (3), 4GB (4), 8GB (5), 10GB (6), 16GB (8). Some of the above values may not be supported by all type of switches.

swFCPortName.name: swFCPortName
swFCPortName.description: A string indicates the name of the addressed port. The names should be persistent across switch reboots. Port names do not have to be unique within a switch or within a fabric.

swFCPortSpecifier.name: swFCPortSpecifier
swFCPortSpecifier.description: This string indicates the physical port number of the addressed port. The format of the string is: <slot>/port, where 'slot' being present only for bladed systems.

swFCPortFlag.name: swFCPortFlag
swFCPortFlag.description: A bit map of port status flags which includes the information of port type. Currently this will indicate if the port is virtual or physical.

swFCPortDisableReason.name: swFCPortDisableReason
swFCPortDisableReason.description: It indicates the state change reason when port goes from online to offline

swNsLocalNumEntry.name: swNsLocalNumEntry
swNsLocalNumEntry.description: The number of local Name Server entries.

swNsLocalTable.name: swNsLocalTable
swNsLocalTable.description: The table of local Name Server entries.

swNsLocalEntry.name: swNsLocalEntry
swNsLocalEntry.description: An entry of the local Name Server database.

swNsEntryIndex.name: swNsEntryIndex
swNsEntryIndex.description: The object identifies the Name Server database entry.

swNsPortID.name: swNsPortID
swNsPortID.description: The object identifies the Fibre Channel port address ID of the entry.

swNsPortType.name: swNsPortType
swNsPortType.description: The object identifies the type of port: N_Port, NL_Port, etc., for this entry. The type is defined in FC-GS-2.

swNsPortName.name: swNsPortName
swNsPortName.description: The object identifies the Fibre Channel World_wide Name of the port entry.

swNsPortSymb.name: swNsPortSymb
swNsPortSymb.description: The object identifies the contents of a Symbolic Name of the port entry. In FC-GS-2, a Symbolic Name consists of a byte array of 1 through 255 bytes, and the first byte of the array specifies the length of its 'contents'. This object variable corresponds to the 'contents' of the Symbolic Name, without the first byte.

swNsNodeName.name: swNsNodeName
swNsNodeName.description: The object identifies the Fibre Channel World_wide Name of the associated node as defined in FC-GS-2.

swNsNodeSymb.name: swNsNodeSymb
swNsNodeSymb.description: The object identifies the contents of a Symbolic Name of the the node associated with the entry. In FC-GS-2, a Symbolic Name consists of a byte array of 1 through 255 bytes, and the first byte of the array specifies the length of its 'contents'. This object variable corresponds to the 'contents' of the Symbolic Name, without the first byte (specifying the length).

swNsIPA.name: swNsIPA
swNsIPA.description: The object identifies the Initial Process Associator of the node for the entry as defined in FC-GS-2.

swNsIpAddress.name: swNsIpAddress
swNsIpAddress.description: The object identifies the IP address of the node for the entry as defined in FC-GS-2. The format of the address is in IPv6.

swNsCos.name: swNsCos
swNsCos.description: The object identifies the class of services supported by the port. The value is a bit-map defined as follows: o bit 0 is class F, o bit 1 is class 1, o bit 2 is class 2, o bit 3 is class 3, o bit 4 is class 4, etc.

swNsFc4.name: swNsFc4
swNsFc4.description: The object identifies the FC-4s supported by the port as defined in FC-GS-2.

swNsIpNxPort.name: swNsIpNxPort
swNsIpNxPort.description: The object identifies IpAddress of the Nx_port for the entry.

swNsWwn.name: swNsWwn
swNsWwn.description: The object identifies the World Wide Name (WWN) of the Fx_port for the entry.

swNsHardAddr.name: swNsHardAddr
swNsHardAddr.description: The object identifies the 24-bit hard address of the node for the entry.

swEventTrapLevel.name: swEventTrapLevel
swEventTrapLevel.description: swAgtTrapSeverityLevel, in absence of swEventTrapLevel, specifies the Trap Severity Level of each defined trap recipient host. This object specifies the swEventTrap level in conjunction with an event's severity level. When an event occurs and if its severity level is at or below the value specified by this object instance, the agent will send the associated swEventTrap to configured recipients.

swEventNumEntries.name: swEventNumEntries
swEventNumEntries.description: The number of entries in the Event Table.

swEventEntry.name: swEventEntry
swEventEntry.description: An entry of the event table.

swEventIndex.name: swEventIndex
swEventIndex.description: This object identifies the event entry.

swEventTimeInfo.name: swEventTimeInfo
swEventTimeInfo.description: This object identifies the date and time when this event occurred, in textual format.

swEventLevel.name: swEventLevel
swEventLevel.description: This object identifies the severity level of this event entry.

swEventRepeatCount.name: swEventRepeatCount
swEventRepeatCount.description: This object identifies how many times this particular event has occurred.

swEventDescr.name: swEventDescr
swEventDescr.description: This object identifies the textual description of the event.

swEventVfId.name: swEventVfId
swEventVfId.description: This object identifies the Virtual fabric id.

swFwClassAreaTable.name: swFwClassAreaTable
swFwClassAreaTable.description: The table of classes and areas.

swFwClassAreaEntry.name: swFwClassAreaEntry
swFwClassAreaEntry.description: An entry of the classes and areas.

swFwClassAreaIndex.name: swFwClassAreaIndex
swFwClassAreaIndex.description: This object identifies the class type.

swFwWriteThVals.name: swFwWriteThVals
swFwWriteThVals.description: This object is set to apply the value changes.

swFwDefaultUnit.name: swFwDefaultUnit
swFwDefaultUnit.description: A Default unit string name for a threshold area.

swFwDefaultTimebase.name: swFwDefaultTimebase
swFwDefaultTimebase.description: A Default timebase for the current threshold counter.

swFwCustUnit.name: swFwCustUnit
swFwCustUnit.description: A custom unit string name for a threshold area.

swFwCustTimebase.name: swFwCustTimebase
swFwCustTimebase.description: A custom timebase for the current threshold counter.

swFwThLevel.name: swFwThLevel
swFwThLevel.description: A level where all the threshold values are set at.

swFwWriteActVals.name: swFwWriteActVals
swFwWriteActVals.description: This object is set to apply act value changes.

swFwDefaultChangedActs.name: swFwDefaultChangedActs
swFwDefaultChangedActs.description: Default action matrix for changed event.

swFwDefaultExceededActs.name: swFwDefaultExceededActs
swFwDefaultExceededActs.description: Default action matrix for exceeded event.

swFwDefaultBelowActs.name: swFwDefaultBelowActs
swFwDefaultBelowActs.description: Default action matrix for below event.

swFwDefaultAboveActs.name: swFwDefaultAboveActs
swFwDefaultAboveActs.description: Default action matrix for above event.

swFwDefaultInBetweenActs.name: swFwDefaultInBetweenActs
swFwDefaultInBetweenActs.description: Default action matrix for in-between event.

swFwCustChangedActs.name: swFwCustChangedActs
swFwCustChangedActs.description: custom action matrix for changed event.

swFwCustExceededActs.name: swFwCustExceededActs
swFwCustExceededActs.description: custom action matrix for exceeded event.

swFwCustBelowActs.name: swFwCustBelowActs
swFwCustBelowActs.description: custom action matrix for below event.

swFwCustAboveActs.name: swFwCustAboveActs
swFwCustAboveActs.description: custom action matrix for above event.

swFwCustInBetweenActs.name: swFwCustInBetweenActs
swFwCustInBetweenActs.description: custom action matrix for in-between event.

swFwValidActs.name: swFwValidActs
swFwValidActs.description: matrix of valid acts for an class/area.

swFwActLevel.name: swFwActLevel
swFwActLevel.description: A level where all the actions are set at.

swFwThresholdEntry.name: swFwThresholdEntry
swFwThresholdEntry.description: An entry of an individual threshold.

swFwThresholdIndex.name: swFwThresholdIndex
swFwThresholdIndex.description: This object identifies the element index of an threshold.

swFwStatus.name: swFwStatus
swFwStatus.description: This object identifies if an threshold is enabled or disabled.

swFwName.name: swFwName
swFwName.description: This object is a name of the threshold.

swFwLabel.name: swFwLabel
swFwLabel.description: This object is a label of the threshold.

swFwCurVal.name: swFwCurVal
swFwCurVal.description: This object is a current counter of the threshold.

swFwLastEvent.name: swFwLastEvent
swFwLastEvent.description: This object is a last event type of the threshold.

swFwLastEventVal.name: swFwLastEventVal
swFwLastEventVal.description: This object is a last event value of the threshold.

swFwLastEventTime.name: swFwLastEventTime
swFwLastEventTime.description: This object is a last event time of the threshold.

swFwLastState.name: swFwLastState
swFwLastState.description: This object is a last event state of the threshold.

swFwBehaviorType.name: swFwBehaviorType
swFwBehaviorType.description: A behavior of which the thresholds generate event.

swFwBehaviorInt.name: swFwBehaviorInt
swFwBehaviorInt.description: A integer of which the thresholds generate continuous event.

swFwLastSeverityLevel.name: swFwLastSeverityLevel
swFwLastSeverityLevel.description: This object is a last event severity level of the threshold.

swEndDeviceRlsTable.name: swEndDeviceRlsTable
swEndDeviceRlsTable.description: The table of individual end devices' rls.

swEndDeviceRlsEntry.name: swEndDeviceRlsEntry
swEndDeviceRlsEntry.description: An entry of an individual end devices' rls.

swEndDevicePort.name: swEndDevicePort
swEndDevicePort.description: This object identifies the port of the end device.

swEndDeviceAlpa.name: swEndDeviceAlpa
swEndDeviceAlpa.description: This object identifies the alpa of the end device.

swEndDevicePortID.name: swEndDevicePortID
swEndDevicePortID.description: The object identifies the Fibre Channel port address ID of the entry.

swEndDeviceLinkFailure.name: swEndDeviceLinkFailure
swEndDeviceLinkFailure.description: Link failure count for the end device.

swEndDeviceSyncLoss.name: swEndDeviceSyncLoss
swEndDeviceSyncLoss.description: Sync loss count for the end device.

swEndDeviceSigLoss.name: swEndDeviceSigLoss
swEndDeviceSigLoss.description: Sig loss count for the end device.

swEndDeviceProtoErr.name: swEndDeviceProtoErr
swEndDeviceProtoErr.description: Protocol err count for the end device.

swEndDeviceInvalidWord.name: swEndDeviceInvalidWord
swEndDeviceInvalidWord.description: Invalid word count for the end device.

swEndDeviceInvalidCRC.name: swEndDeviceInvalidCRC
swEndDeviceInvalidCRC.description: Invalid CRC count for the end device.

swGroupTable.name: swGroupTable
swGroupTable.description: The table of groups. This may not be available on all versions of Fabric OS.

swGroupEntry.name: swGroupEntry
swGroupEntry.description: An entry of table of groups.

swGroupIndex.name: swGroupIndex
swGroupIndex.description: This object is the group index starting from 1.

swGroupName.name: swGroupName
swGroupName.description: This object identifies the name of the group.

swGroupType.name: swGroupType
swGroupType.description: This object identifies the type of the group.

swGroupMemTable.name: swGroupMemTable
swGroupMemTable.description: The table of members of all groups. This may not be available on all versions of Fabric OS.

swGroupMemEntry.name: swGroupMemEntry
swGroupMemEntry.description: An entry for a member of a group.

swGroupId.name: swGroupId
swGroupId.description: This object identifies the Group Id of the member switch.

swGroupMemWwn.name: swGroupMemWwn
swGroupMemWwn.description: This object identifies the WWN of the member switch.

swGroupMemPos.name: swGroupMemPos
swGroupMemPos.description: This object identifies position of the member switch in the group. This is based on the order that the switches were added in the group.

swBlmPerfALPAMntEntry.name: swBlmPerfALPAMntEntry
swBlmPerfALPAMntEntry.description: ALPA monitoring counter for given ALPA.

swBlmPerfAlpaPort.name: swBlmPerfAlpaPort
swBlmPerfAlpaPort.description: This Object identifies the port index of the switch.

swBlmPerfAlpaIndx.name: swBlmPerfAlpaIndx
swBlmPerfAlpaIndx.description: This Object identifies the ALPA index. There can be 126 ALPA values

swBlmPerfAlpa.name: swBlmPerfAlpa
swBlmPerfAlpa.description: This Object identifies the ALPA values. These values range between x'01' and x'EF'(1 to 239). ALPA value x'00' is reserved for FL_Port If Alpa device is invalid, then it will have -1 value.

swBlmPerfAlpaCRCCnt.name: swBlmPerfAlpaCRCCnt
swBlmPerfAlpaCRCCnt.description: Get CRC count for given ALPA and port. This monitoring provides information on the number of CRC errors occurred on the frames destined to each possible ALPA attached to a specific port.

swBlmPerfEEMntEntry.name: swBlmPerfEEMntEntry
swBlmPerfEEMntEntry.description: End-to-End monitoring counter for given port.

swBlmPerfEEPort.name: swBlmPerfEEPort
swBlmPerfEEPort.description: This object identifies the port number of the switch.

swBlmPerfEERefKey.name: swBlmPerfEERefKey
swBlmPerfEERefKey.description: This object identifies the reference number of the counter. This reference is number assigned when a filter is created. In SNMP Index start one instead of 0, add one to actual ref key

swBlmPerfEECRC.name: swBlmPerfEECRC
swBlmPerfEECRC.description: Get End to End CRC error for the frames that matched the SID-DID pair.

swBlmPerfEEFCWRx.name: swBlmPerfEEFCWRx
swBlmPerfEEFCWRx.description: Get End to End count of Fibre Channel words (FCW), received by the port, that matched the SID-DID pair.

swBlmPerfEEFCWTx.name: swBlmPerfEEFCWTx
swBlmPerfEEFCWTx.description: Get End to End count of Fibre Channel words (FCW), transmitted by the port, that matched the SID-DID pair.

swBlmPerfEESid.name: swBlmPerfEESid
swBlmPerfEESid.description: Gets SID info by reference number. SID (Source Identifier) is a 3-byte field in the frame header used to indicate the address identifier of the N-Port from which the frame was sent.

swBlmPerfEEDid.name: swBlmPerfEEDid
swBlmPerfEEDid.description: Gets DID info by reference number. DID (Destination Identifier) is a 3-byte field in the frame header used to indicate the address identifier of the N-Port to which the frame was sent.

swBlmPerfFltMntEntry.name: swBlmPerfFltMntEntry
swBlmPerfFltMntEntry.description: Filter base monitoring counter for given port.

swBlmPerfFltPort.name: swBlmPerfFltPort
swBlmPerfFltPort.description: This object identifies the port number of the switch.

swBlmPerfFltRefkey.name: swBlmPerfFltRefkey
swBlmPerfFltRefkey.description: This object identifies the reference number of the filter. This reference number is assigned when a filter is created. In SNMP Index start one instead of 0, add one to actual ref key

swBlmPerfFltCnt.name: swBlmPerfFltCnt
swBlmPerfFltCnt.description: Get statistics of filter based monitor. Filter based monitoring provides information about a filter hit count such as 1. Read command 2. SCSI or IP traffic 3. SCSI Read/Write

swSwitchTrunkable.name: swSwitchTrunkable
swSwitchTrunkable.description: The trunking status of the switch - whether the switch supports the trunking feature or not. The values are yes(8) - the trunking feature is supported no(0). - the trunking feature is not supported.

swTrunkTable.name: swTrunkTable
swTrunkTable.description: Table to display trunking information for the switch.

swTrunkPortIndex.name: swTrunkPortIndex
swTrunkPortIndex.description: This object identifies the switch port index. Note that the value of a port index is 1 higher than the port number labeled on the front panel. e.g. port index 1 correspond to port number 0.

swTrunkGroupNumber.name: swTrunkGroupNumber
swTrunkGroupNumber.description: This object is a logical entity which specifies the Group Number to which the port belongs to. If this value is Zero it means the port is not Trunked.

swTrunkMaster.name: swTrunkMaster
swTrunkMaster.description: Port number that is the trunk master of the group. The trunk master implicitly defines the group. All ports with the same master are considered to be part of the same group.

swPortTrunked.name: swPortTrunked
swPortTrunked.description: The active trunk status for a member port. Values are enabled(1) or disabled(0).

swTrunkGrpTable.name: swTrunkGrpTable
swTrunkGrpTable.description: Table to display trunking Performance information for the switch.

swTrunkGrpEntry.name: swTrunkGrpEntry
swTrunkGrpEntry.description: Entry for the trunking Group table.

swTrunkGrpNumber.name: swTrunkGrpNumber
swTrunkGrpNumber.description: This object is a logical entity which specifies the Group Number to which port belongs to.

swTrunkGrpMaster.name: swTrunkGrpMaster
swTrunkGrpMaster.description: This object gives the master port id for the TrunkGroup.

swTrunkGrpTx.name: swTrunkGrpTx
swTrunkGrpTx.description: Gives the aggregate value of the transmitted words from this TrunkGroup.

swTrunkGrpRx.name: swTrunkGrpRx
swTrunkGrpRx.description: Gives the aggregate value of the received words by this TrunkGroup.

swTopTalkerMntMode.name: swTopTalkerMntMode
swTopTalkerMntMode.description: Gives the mode in which toptalker is installed

swTopTalkerMntNumEntries.name: swTopTalkerMntNumEntries
swTopTalkerMntNumEntries.description: Gives the number of toptalking flows

swTopTalkerMntIndex.name: swTopTalkerMntIndex
swTopTalkerMntIndex.description: This object identifies the list/object entry

swTopTalkerMntPort.name: swTopTalkerMntPort
swTopTalkerMntPort.description: This object identifies the switch port number on which the f-port mode toptalker is added.

swTopTalkerMntSpid.name: swTopTalkerMntSpid
swTopTalkerMntSpid.description: This object identifies the SID of the host

swTopTalkerMntDpid.name: swTopTalkerMntDpid
swTopTalkerMntDpid.description: This object identifies the DID of the SID-DID pair

swTopTalkerMntflow.name: swTopTalkerMntflow
swTopTalkerMntflow.description: This object identifies the traffic flow in MB/sec

swTopTalkerMntSwwn.name: swTopTalkerMntSwwn
swTopTalkerMntSwwn.description: This object identifies the SID in WWN format of the host

swTopTalkerMntDwwn.name: swTopTalkerMntDwwn
swTopTalkerMntDwwn.description: This object identifies the DID in WWN format of the SID-DID pair

swCpuNoOfRetries.name: swCpuNoOfRetries
swCpuNoOfRetries.description: Number of times system should take cpu utilization sample before sending the CPU utilization trap.

swCpuUsageLimit.name: swCpuUsageLimit
swCpuUsageLimit.description: CPU usage limit. If MAPS is enabled, then this object is not supported and return 0 value.

swCpuPollingInterval.name: swCpuPollingInterval
swCpuPollingInterval.description: Time interval between two memory samples.

swCpuAction.name: swCpuAction
swCpuAction.description: Specifies the actions to be taken if system resources exceed the specified threshold. If MAPS is enabled, then this object is not supported and return 0 value.

swMemNoOfRetries.name: swMemNoOfRetries
swMemNoOfRetries.description: Number of times system should take memory usage sample before sending the memory usage trap.

swMemPollingInterval.name: swMemPollingInterval
swMemPollingInterval.description: Time interval between two memory samples.

swMemAction.name: swMemAction
swMemAction.description: Specifies the actions to be taken if system resources exceed the specified threshold. If MAPS is enabled, then this object is not supported and return 0 value.

swMemUsageLimit1.name: swMemUsageLimit1
swMemUsageLimit1.description: Low memory usage limit. If MAPS is enabled, then this object is not supported and return 0 value.

swMemUsageLimit3.name: swMemUsageLimit3
swMemUsageLimit3.description: High memory usage limit. If MAPS is enabled, then this object is not supported and return 0 value.

swConnUnitPortStatEntry.name: swConnUnitPortStatEntry
swConnUnitPortStatEntry.description: This represents the Conn unit Port Stats

swConnUnitCRCWithBadEOF.name: swConnUnitCRCWithBadEOF
swConnUnitCRCWithBadEOF.description: The number of frames with CRC error with Bad EOF.

swConnUnitZeroTenancy.name: swConnUnitZeroTenancy
swConnUnitZeroTenancy.description: This counter is incremented when the FL_port acquires the loop but does not transmit a frame.

swConnUnitFLNumOfTenancy.name: swConnUnitFLNumOfTenancy
swConnUnitFLNumOfTenancy.description: This counter is incremented when the FL_port acquires the loop.

swConnUnitNLNumOfTenancy.name: swConnUnitNLNumOfTenancy
swConnUnitNLNumOfTenancy.description: This counter is incremented when the NL_port acquires the loop.

swConnUnitStopTenancyStarVation.name: swConnUnitStopTenancyStarVation
swConnUnitStopTenancyStarVation.description: This counter is incremented when the FL_port can not transmit a frame because of lack of credit.

swConnUnitOpend.name: swConnUnitOpend
swConnUnitOpend.description: The number of times FC port entered OPENED state.

swConnUnitTransferConnection.name: swConnUnitTransferConnection
swConnUnitTransferConnection.description: The number of times FC port entered TRANSFER state.

swConnUnitOpen.name: swConnUnitOpen
swConnUnitOpen.description: The number of times FC port entered OPEN state.

swConnUnitInvalidARB.name: swConnUnitInvalidARB
swConnUnitInvalidARB.description: The number of times FC port received invalid ARB.

swConnUnitFTB1Miss.name: swConnUnitFTB1Miss
swConnUnitFTB1Miss.description: This counter is incremented when the port receives a frame with a DID that can not be routed by FCR.. Applicable to 8G platforms only.

swConnUnitFTB2Miss.name: swConnUnitFTB2Miss
swConnUnitFTB2Miss.description: This counter is incremented when the port receives a frame with an SID/DID combination that can not be routed by the VF module.Applicable to 8G platforms only.

swConnUnitFTB6Miss.name: swConnUnitFTB6Miss
swConnUnitFTB6Miss.description: This counter is incremented when port receives a frame with an SID that can not be routed by FCR. Applicable to 8G platforms.

swConnUnitZoneMiss.name: swConnUnitZoneMiss
swConnUnitZoneMiss.description: This counter is incremented when the port receives a frame with an SID and DID that are not zoned together.

swConnUnitLunZoneMiss.name: swConnUnitLunZoneMiss
swConnUnitLunZoneMiss.description: This counter is incremented when the port receives a frame with an SID, DID and LUN that are not zoned together( This is not currently used ).

swConnUnitBadEOF.name: swConnUnitBadEOF
swConnUnitBadEOF.description: The number of frames with bad end-of-frame.

swConnUnitLCRX.name: swConnUnitLCRX
swConnUnitLCRX.description: The number of link control frames received.

swConnUnitRDYPriority.name: swConnUnitRDYPriority
swConnUnitRDYPriority.description: The number of times that sending R_RDY or VC_RDY primitive signals was a higher priority than sending frames, due to diminishing credit reserves in the transmitter at the other end of the fibre.

swConnUnitLli.name: swConnUnitLli
swConnUnitLli.description: The number low level interrupts generated by the physical and link layer.

swConnUnitInterrupts.name: swConnUnitInterrupts
swConnUnitInterrupts.description: This represents all the interrupts received on a port. Includes LLI, unknown etc

swConnUnitUnknownInterrupts.name: swConnUnitUnknownInterrupts
swConnUnitUnknownInterrupts.description: Represents all the unknown interrupts received on a port.

swConnUnitTimedOut.name: swConnUnitTimedOut
swConnUnitTimedOut.description: Represents number of timed out frames due to any reason.

swConnUnitProcRequired.name: swConnUnitProcRequired
swConnUnitProcRequired.description: Represents number of frames trapped by CPU.

swConnUnitTxBufferUnavailable.name: swConnUnitTxBufferUnavailable
swConnUnitTxBufferUnavailable.description: Number of times port failed to transmit frames .

swConnUnitStateChange.name: swConnUnitStateChange
swConnUnitStateChange.description: Number of times port has gone to offline, online, and faulty state.

swConnUnitC3DiscardDueToRXTimeout.name: swConnUnitC3DiscardDueToRXTimeout
swConnUnitC3DiscardDueToRXTimeout.description: Number of Class 3 receive frames discarded due to timeout.

swConnUnitC3DiscardDueToDestUnreachable.name: swConnUnitC3DiscardDueToDestUnreachable
swConnUnitC3DiscardDueToDestUnreachable.description: Number of Class 3 frames discarded due to destination unreachable.

swConnUnitC3DiscardDueToTXTimeout.name: swConnUnitC3DiscardDueToTXTimeout
swConnUnitC3DiscardDueToTXTimeout.description: Number of Class 3 transmit frames discarded due to timeout.

swConnUnitC3DiscardOther.name: swConnUnitC3DiscardOther
swConnUnitC3DiscardOther.description: Number of Class 3 frames discarded due to unknow reasons.

swConnUnitPCSErrorCounter.name: swConnUnitPCSErrorCounter
swConnUnitPCSErrorCounter.description: Number of Physical coding sublayer(PCS) block errors. It records the encoding violations on 10G or 16Gbps port.

swConnUnitFECCorrectedCounter.name: swConnUnitFECCorrectedCounter
swConnUnitFECCorrectedCounter.description: It indicates Forward Error Correction Corrected Blocks count.FEC feature is only applicable to 10G/16G platforms.

swConnUnitFECUnCorrectedCounter.name: swConnUnitFECUnCorrectedCounter
swConnUnitFECUnCorrectedCounter.description: It indicates Forward Error Correction UnCorrected Blocks count.FEC feature is only applicable to 10G/16G platforms.

swTrapsV2.name: swTrapsV2
swTrapsV2.description: The Traps for Brocade's Fibre Channel Switch.

swFault.name: swFault
swFault.description: Obsoleted this trap as firmware doesn't support this trap. A swFault(1) is generated whenever the diagnostics detects a fault with the switch.

swSensorScn.name: swSensorScn
swSensorScn.description: A swSensorScn(2) is generated whenever an environment sensor changes its operational state. For instance, a fan stop working. The VarBind in the Trap Data Unit shall contain the corresponding instance of the sensor status, sensor index, sensor type, sensor value (reading) and sensor information. Note that the sensor information contains the type of sensor and its number in textual format.

swFCPortScn.name: swFCPortScn
swFCPortScn.description: This trap is sent whenever an FC port operational status or its type changed. The events that trigger this trap are port goes to online/offline, port type changed to E-port/F-port/FL-port. swFCPortName and swSsn are optional varbind in the trap PDU

swEventTrap.name: swEventTrap
swEventTrap.description: This trap is generated when an event whose level at or below swEventTrapLevel occurs.

swFabricWatchTrap.name: swFabricWatchTrap
swFabricWatchTrap.description: trap to be sent by Fabric Watch to notify of an event.

swTrackChangesTrap.name: swTrackChangesTrap
swTrackChangesTrap.description: trap to be sent for tracking login/logout/config changes.

swIPv6ChangeTrap.name: swIPv6ChangeTrap
swIPv6ChangeTrap.description: This trap is generated when an ipv6 address status change event occurs.

swPmgrEventTrap.name: swPmgrEventTrap
swPmgrEventTrap.description: This trap is generated when any partition manager change happens.

swFabricReconfigTrap.name: swFabricReconfigTrap
swFabricReconfigTrap.description: trap to be sent for tracking fabric reconfiguration
